name: Insurrection Omega
description: Mirror Lorca has obtained his own ship with the help of an invincible crew: the holograms of the Insurrection Alpha program. Can you find a way to take back this warship version of Voyager and stop Lorca's conquest before it starts?
rules:
-- In a Skirmish Event, you will engage in space battles against thematically appropriate foes until the Event's conclusion.
-- There are two Phases to this Event! Each Phase is individually timed.
-- Unique Ship Battle Missions are available during the event. Open the Event to access them.
-- Using any version of Seska, T. Paris, Lorca, or matching a Battle Trait will provide a bonus.
-- Using the Warship Voyager, La Sirena, or Val Jean will provide a bonus to hull.
-- Every Ship Battle you win earns you Event Victory Points. Collect Event Victory Points to unlock Threshold Rewards!
-- In this event, Squadrons may also compete to advance up the Squadron leaderboards. Join a Squadron to get more rewards!
bonus_text: Crew Bonus: Seska, T. Paris, or Lorca

screens.text: "Gabriel Lorca, you have unlawfully seized the Federation starship Voyager. You will surrender now, or face additional charges in a Federation court upon capture."

"This isn't a Federation starship. It's packed with ordnance, cannons, weapons of war. Why shouldn't I take it? You wouldn't know what to do with it... or maybe you would, seeing as its your very angry Maquis holograms who helped me take it."

"Regret is an illogical emotion, but I experience it most often regarding my Insurrection Alpha holoprogram. Lorca has, with the help of its characters, taken control of this alternate Voyager. Being of the Terran Empire, his intentions cannot be good. We must retake the ship."
